        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: resolve ACP delivery threadId from session deliveryContext",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nACP sessions (e.g. Discord delivery via ACP) fail to route replies because `resolveRoutedDeliveryThreadId` cannot extract a `threadId` from ACP session keys. The function's three-tier fallback chain — `MessageThreadId` → `TransportThreadId` → `parseSessionThreadInfoFast` — all return nothing because:\n\n1. `MessageThreadId` and `TransportThreadId` are null when delivering through the ACP coordinator\n2. `parseSessionThreadInfoFast` parses thread info from `:thread:` suffix, but ACP session keys use `agent:<id>:acp:<uuid>` format\n\nHowever, the session entry's `deliveryContext.threadId` IS already set during ACP spawn (`src/gateway/server-methods/agent.ts` adds it via `requestDeliveryHint`), and `preparedSessionState.sessionEntry` is available at the call site. The data was there — it just wasn't being used.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe fix adds a `deliveryThreadId` parameter to `resolveRoutedDeliveryThreadId` that slots between the inbound thread id checks and the session-key parse:\n\n```\nMessageThreadId → TransportThreadId → deliveryThreadId (NEW) → parseSessionThreadInfoFast\n```\n\nPlaced before `parseSessionThreadInfoFast` because `deliveryContext.threadId` is authoritatively set by the gateway during spawn and is more reliable than parsing session key conventions.\n\nOnly the `get-reply-run.ts` call site is wired up (the entry point that feeds thread context into `createAcpDispatchDeliveryCoordinator`). The `dispatch-from-config.ts` call site is intentionally not changed — it has a comment warning that reading from `deliveryContext` can resurrect stale routes.\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Existing tests pass\n```\n$ npx vitest run src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-acp-delivery.test.ts --no-coverage\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  31 passed (31)\n\n$ npx vitest run src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts --no-coverage -t \"thread\"\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  6 passed | 217 skipped (223)\n```\n\n### Source-level proof\nThe `resolveRoutedDeliveryThreadId(\"uses session key thread id suffix\")` test continues to pass — the new parameter is optional and doesn't affect existing callers.\n\nThe gateway already writes `deliveryContext.threadId` during ACP spawn (`src/gateway/server-methods/agent.ts`, via `requestDeliveryHint`). The fix simply reads what's already there through the same `string | number` path used by the existing `MessageThreadId`/`TransportThreadId` fallbacks.\n\n### Not tested\n- End-to-end ACP Discord delivery with a real Discord channel (requires live Discord + agent infrastructure)\n\n## Merge Risk\n\n**Low**. The change:\n- Adds one optional parameter (no existing callers broken)\n- Reads `deliveryContext?.threadId` from an already-loaded session entry (no new IO)\n- Uses the same `string | number` type already supported by the function\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
